50|$|The {{dominant}} {{cause of}} soil displacement in frost heaving {{is the development}} of <b>ice</b> <b>lenses.</b> During frost heave, one or more soil-free <b>ice</b> <b>lenses</b> grow, and their growth displaces the soil above them. These lenses grow by the continual addition of water from a groundwater source that is lower in the soil and below the freezing line in the soil. The presence of frost-susceptible soil with a pore structure that allows capillary flow is essential to supplying water to the <b>ice</b> <b>lenses</b> as they form.|$|R
